{"lemma":"أَصْغَرانِ","slug":"أَصْغَرانِ","root":"ص.غ.ر","root_slug":"ص-غ-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ص-غ-ر","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَصْغَر","root":"صغر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n24387"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B5%D9%92%D8%BA%D9%8E%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of صَغِير (ṣaḡīr):; smaller; smallest"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"elative degree of صَغِير (ṣaḡīr):; younger; youngest"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"lesser (of two, or rarely more than two, things: the smaller in size, in value, in importance etc.)"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"junior (age, rank, etc.)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to reduce, to diminish"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to demean, to degrade; to belittle, to humiliate, to disparage"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Elative of صَغِير (ṣaḡīr, “small, young”).\n\nCausative of صَغُرَ (ṣaḡura, “to be or become small”) and صَغِرَ (ṣaḡira, “to be or become small”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n24387","headword_ar":"اَصْغَرُ","root":"Sgr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Smaller,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"less;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"smallest,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"least; in body,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corporeal substance;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in estimation"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rank"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dignity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in years,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"age"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, Msb, K:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SugoraY","text_ar":"صُغْرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) pl. masc."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAgiru","text_ar":"اَصَاغِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sb, S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSaAgirapN","text_ar":"اَصَاغِرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) though the sing. is not of the nouns which regularly add"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"to the pl., and it is added in this case because the sing. resembles in form"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qa$oEamN","text_ar":"قَشْعَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qa$aAEimapN","text_ar":"قَشَاعِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl., (ISd,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSogaruwna","text_ar":"اَصْغَرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sb, S:) and pl. fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SugarN","text_ar":"صُغَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sb, S, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SugorayaAtN","text_ar":"صُغْرَيَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) but Sb says, you do not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nisowapN SugarN","text_ar":"نِسْوَةٌ صُغَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", nor"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qawomN A^aSaAgiru","text_ar":"قَوْمٌ اَصَاغِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", except with the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":": and he adds, we have heard the Arabs says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSaAgiru","text_ar":"الاَصَاغِرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[perhaps miswritten for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSaAgirapu","text_ar":"الاَصَاغِرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and if you please, you may say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSogaruwna","text_ar":"الاَصْغَرُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aSogaraAni","text_ar":"الاَصْغَرَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The two less,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"least, things,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the heart and the tongue."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almaro'u biA^aSogarayohi","text_ar":"المَرْءُ بِاَصْغَرَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The man"},{"kind":"text","text":"obtains power over things, and manages them thoroughly,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by means of his heart and his tongue."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, TA. [See Har p. 446.]) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SagiyrN","text_ar":"صَغِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","Sb","M","ISd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}